---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'safetywing', text: 'SafetyWing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'allianz-care', text: 'Allianz Care', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'student-needs', text: 'Student-Specific Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Student Insurance Guide', href: '/insurance-for/students' },
  { title: 'Study Abroad Insurance', href: '/best/study-abroad-insurance' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Insurance Type', safetywing: 'Travel medical', cigna: 'Health insurance', allianz: 'Health insurance' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', safetywing: '$250,000', cigna: 'Unlimited', allianz: '€1M - €3M' },
  { feature: 'Monthly Price (Age 22)', safetywing: '$45-55', cigna: '$180-280', allianz: '$120-180' },
  { feature: 'Visa Compliant', safetywing: 'Sometimes', cigna: 'Yes', allianz: 'Yes' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', safetywing: 'Crisis only', cigna: 'Good', allianz: 'Best' },
  { feature: 'Flexibility', safetywing: 'Monthly', cigna: 'Annual', allianz: 'Annual' },
  { feature: 'Routine Care', safetywing: 'Limited', cigna: 'Included', allianz: 'Included' },
  { feature: 'Best For', safetywing: 'Budget/short-term', cigna: 'Full coverage', allianz: 'Best value' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Student, Age 20', safetywing: '$45/mo', cigna: '$150-220/mo', allianz: '$100-150/mo' },
  { profile: 'Student, Age 25', safetywing: '$50/mo', cigna: '$180-280/mo', allianz: '$120-180/mo' },
  { profile: 'Graduate, Age 28', safetywing: '$55/mo', cigna: '$220-320/mo', allianz: '$140-200/mo' },
  { profile: 'Full Year Cost (Age 22)', safetywing: '$550-600', cigna: '$2,000-3,000', allianz: '$1,400-2,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing vs Cigna vs Allianz: Best Student Insurance Abroad 2026"
  description="Compare insurance for students studying abroad: SafetyWing, Cigna Global, and Allianz Care. Budget travel medical vs comprehensive health insurance for international students."
  headline="SafetyWing vs Cigna vs Allianz: Student Insurance Compared"
  subheadline="From budget travel medical to comprehensive health coverage—three tiers of protection for students and young professionals abroad."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-amber-50 border-2 border-amber-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Budget Option</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">SafetyWing</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">$45/mo. Emergency coverage only. May not meet visa requirements. Best for short exchanges or gap years.</p>
      <a href="/go/safetywing" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get SafetyWing Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Value</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Real health insurance at student-friendly prices. Visa compliant. Best mental health benefits.</p>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Premium Choice</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Best coverage and service. Unlimited limits. Worth it if parents are paying or you have ongoing health needs.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    Students have tight budgets but real health needs—especially mental health support away from home. SafetyWing is cheapest but limited. Allianz offers the best balance of coverage and cost. Cigna is premium but comprehensive.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="safetywing">SafetyWing</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Cheapest</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Monthly Billing</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Flexible</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    SafetyWing at $45/month is the most affordable option—appealing for students on tight budgets. But it's travel medical insurance, not health insurance. Emergency coverage only, limited mental health, and may not meet visa requirements for student visas.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Only $45-55/month</li>
    <li>Monthly subscription—no annual commitment</li>
    <li>Simple signup, instant coverage</li>
    <li>Good for emergencies abroad</li>
    <li>30 days home country coverage included</li>
    <li>Flexible for semester or gap year</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Travel medical, not health insurance</li>
    <li>May not meet student visa requirements</li>
    <li>$250K limit (low for serious illness)</li>
    <li>Mental health: crisis only</li>
    <li>No routine care coverage</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions excluded</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Short exchange programs. Gap year travelers. Students whose visa accepts travel insurance. Budget-conscious with no health conditions.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/safetywing" class="inline-block bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get SafetyWing Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/safetywing" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Coverage</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Visa Compliant</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best App</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global is the premium choice—unlimited coverage, largest network, best app. More expensive, but worth it if you have ongoing health needs, parents are funding it, or your university recommends comprehensive coverage.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Unlimited annual coverage</li>
    <li>Best mobile app for managing care</li>
    <li>Meets all student visa requirements</li>
    <li>Comprehensive routine care included</li>
    <li>Good mental health coverage</li>
    <li>Largest provider network</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most expensive ($2,000-3,000/year)</li>
    <li>Annual commitment required</li>
    <li>May be overkill for healthy students</li>
    <li>24-month mental health waiting period</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Students with ongoing health needs. Those with parent support on costs. Multi-year degree programs. Anyone wanting the best possible coverage.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="allianz-care">Allianz Care</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Value</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Mental Health</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Visa Compliant</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Allianz Care hits the sweet spot for students: real health insurance with comprehensive coverage at 30-40% less than Cigna. Best mental health benefits (important for students away from home), visa compliant, and flexible on pre-existing conditions.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>30-40% cheaper than Cigna</li>
    <li>Best mental health coverage</li>
    <li>Meets student visa requirements</li>
    <li>Routine care included</li>
    <li>12-month mental health waiting period (shorter than Cigna)</li>
    <li>Moratorium underwriting option</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>€3M limit (vs unlimited)</li>
    <li>Smaller network than Cigna</li>
    <li>App less polished</li>
    <li>Annual commitment typically required</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Students who need real insurance but have budget constraints. Anyone prioritizing mental health coverage. Multi-year programs where value matters.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/allianz-care" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Student Options"
    description="Get quotes based on your destination, study duration, and visa requirements."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    Cost matters for students. SafetyWing saves $1,000-2,000/year compared to comprehensive options—but provides less coverage. Allianz offers middle ground.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated prices for healthy students. Annual costs assume 12 months coverage. Excludes US coverage.
  </p>

  <h2 id="student-needs">What Students Need to Consider</h2>

  <h3>Visa Requirements</h3>
  <p>
    Most student visas require health insurance. Check your specific requirements:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> May not meet requirements—travel medical ≠ health insurance</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Meets all standard student visa requirements</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Meets all standard student visa requirements</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Mental Health</h3>
  <p>
    Being away from home is hard. Mental health support matters:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Crisis coverage only—no ongoing therapy</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Good coverage after 24-month waiting period</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Best coverage, 12-month waiting period</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>University Insurance Requirements</h3>
  <p>
    Many universities require proof of insurance or offer their own plans. Compare:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>University plans may be mandatory or can be waived with proof of equivalent coverage</li>
    <li>Check if Cigna/Allianz qualify to waive university insurance</li>
    <li>SafetyWing often doesn't qualify as equivalent coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Coverage During Breaks</h3>
  <p>
    Will you travel during holidays?
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Covers travel anywhere, includes home country visits</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna/Allianz:</strong> Worldwide coverage included in comprehensive plans</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose SafetyWing if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are on a very tight budget</li>
        <li>Are doing a short exchange (semester or less)</li>
        <li>Your visa accepts travel insurance</li>
        <li>Are young and healthy with no conditions</li>
        <li>Just want emergency coverage</li>
        <li>Don't need mental health support</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Allianz Care if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want real insurance at reasonable cost</li>
        <li>Need visa-compliant coverage</li>
        <li>Prioritize mental health support</li>
        <li>Are studying for multiple years</li>
        <li>Want routine care covered</li>
        <li>Have some budget flexibility</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Have ongoing health needs</li>
        <li>Parents are funding your coverage</li>
        <li>Want the best possible protection</li>
        <li>Value the best digital experience</li>
        <li>Are doing a multi-year program</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Will SafetyWing meet my student visa requirements?</h3>
  <p>
    Often no. Most student visas require "health insurance," and SafetyWing is technically "travel medical insurance." Some countries may accept it, but many (Germany, France, Spain, UK) require comprehensive health coverage. Check your specific visa requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use my parents' insurance abroad?</h3>
  <p>
    US-based plans typically don't cover care abroad except emergencies. Even if they do, network access and direct billing won't work. Get dedicated international coverage for your study period.
  </p>

  <h3>What about my university's insurance plan?</h3>
  <p>
    Compare it with these options. University plans are sometimes expensive or limited. Many universities let you waive their plan if you show equivalent coverage. Cigna and Allianz typically qualify; SafetyWing usually doesn't.
  </p>

  <h3>Should I get coverage before I leave or after arrival?</h3>
  <p>
    Get coverage before departure. You need it for visa applications, and you'll be covered during travel. Never leave home without insurance in place.
  </p>

  <h3>What happens if I develop a condition while studying?</h3>
  <p>
    Conditions that develop while you're insured are covered. This is why having good coverage from the start matters—if you start with SafetyWing and develop a condition, upgrading later becomes complicated.
  </p>

  <h3>Is mental health coverage really that important?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. Studies show international students have higher rates of anxiety and depression. Being away from home support systems is challenging. Allianz's strong mental health coverage is a real advantage.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Check your specific visa and university requirements carefully. Coverage terms vary—verify directly with each insurer before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
